Enugu State Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi has emphasized the importance of peace in the progress of the state, insisting that it is a stepping stone to rapid development. Also, Governor Ugwuanyi said he is a governor for everybody, irrespective of class, religion or political leanings. The governor, who spoke at a civic reception and endorsement rally for his re-election in 2019, by the people of Eha-Alumona in Nsukka Local Government Area, thanked them for their honour, solidarity and support. Ugwuanyi  commended the Chairman of the state’s Internal Revenue Services, Prince Emeka Odoh, who is also an illustrious son of the community, for his outstanding performance in office, which he said was responsible for the significant increase in the Internally Generated Revenue (IGR) of the state.